    "Phase one (february to mid-march): procrastinationHKU is widely regarded as one of the three leading universities in Hong Kong; therefore, it is not a surprise that they are the first to come up and announced their stands in Mid-February.",
    "The university had decided to adopt short-term measures by temporarily banning the use of ChatGPT in all classes or forms of assignment for the rest of the semester [57], this was decided because it was in the middle of the semester, so the university believes it is better not to abruptly implement new university policies.",
    "At that time, only Lignan University made a similar response.",
    "Other universities vaguely reply that they value academic integrity, but there was no definite plan announced and they needed more time to study the relevant issues.Not only until early March, the other two leading public universities, HKUST and CUHK, make their announcement on the same day, both decided to allow teachers to flexibly decide whether to restrict students' use of AI-generated tools • Any suspected violations of ban will be treated as cases of plagiarism 27 Feb 2023 LU • Temporarily banning students from using ChatGPT or other AI tools in class and all forms of assignments for this semester Fung [16] (1)• Any suspected violations of ban will be treated as cases of plagiarism Chow [12] (1)1 June HKUST• Launched HKUST ChatGPT for teachers and students for one year Fung [18] (2)based on the nature of their courses and assessments as short-term measures in that semester.",
    "To elaborate, HKUST requires teaching staff to choose one of four options for their course [58], including (i) not restricting the use of generative AI, (ii) only restricting generative AI in assessment, (iii) only restricting designated generative AI in assessment, and (iv) restricting all kinds of generative AI in the course."
